    <note>Jin(1) Yuan [24829] He served in personnel administration. No terminal entry for service in State Council so he may have died in office. See also documentation for father, Daheng [24828]. Yuan is listed as a Qiantang (Hangxian) jinshi in Zhejiang TZ, 127.6a and in CBD, but his name does not appear in the Xianchun Linan zhi or the Jinhua local histories, which confirms the move. His father's funerary inscription notes that he accompanied Chen(1) Liang on his travels. CBD, 2, 1421.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1244:  Apt. Qianshu Shumi yuan shi (State Council)</note>
